article.headline: Bowling Green 63, Northern Colorado 53
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Martin Samarco had 22 points and five rebounds to lead Bowling Green over Northern Colorado 63-53 Tuesday night. Ryne Hamblet added a career-high 20 points and four rebounds off the bench for the Falcons (6-3). A Hamblet 3-pointer in the first half broke a 15-15 tie. It was the start of a 15-4 run for the Falcons that put them up 30-19 at the half and gave them the lead for good. Kirk Archibeque led the Bears with 17 points and nine rebounds, and Dwayne Birden added 10 points and 10 rebounds. Sean Taibi had 14 points for Northern Colorado (2-9). Bowling Green was 19-of-50 for 38 percent shooting, while the Bears were 16-of-47 for 34 percent. Northern Colorado outrebounded the Falcons 39-27. Bowling Green went 18-of-22 from the free throw line.
